 Default Glider (SAFER)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;: Will use the edited animations used on this mod until version 8.4; use this option if you're playing +30fps and getting animation glitches.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_17d.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;i&gt;[&lt;u&gt;replacement&lt;/u&gt;]&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Flower Glider with custom animations&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;The default glider will be replaced with a pretty big flower and custom girly animations. Credits: Initial concept by&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/2017627"&gt;ElizaPeachy&lt;/a&gt;, initial 3D design by&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1739516"&gt;Sockpoppet&lt;/a&gt;, main animation by&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1704241"&gt;banan039&lt;/a&gt;, flower redesign &amp;amp; animations &amp;amp; icon by&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1750563"&gt;i2m&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_17e.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;i&gt;[&lt;u&gt;replacement&lt;/u&gt;]&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Linkle 3 Umbrella with custom animations&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Linkle 3 and her umbrella paraglider replacement, now with icon and physics on the cloth. As they stated, it's a work in progress and some scenes may not align with it installed, but nothing game-breaking.&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap17def.apng"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Default Glider&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;The default Link's paraglider animations will be used.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;16. Other game edited animations&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_18a1.apng"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_18a2.apng"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;default &amp;amp; edit&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap16def.apng"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_16a2.apng"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;default &amp;amp; edit&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap19a.apng"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap19b.apng"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;other&amp;nbsp;edits&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Full Girly edited animations *&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;The whole pack of edited animations, about &lt;b&gt;180 default game animations &lt;/b&gt;changed to look more girly while drawing and holding and hiding weapons, end being tired, crouching,&amp;nbsp;jumping, using and showing the Slate, opening chests and doors, picking objects, teleporting... &lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;Please note:&lt;/b&gt; A random trembling may occur on the arms on certain animations &lt;i&gt;(picking/throwing objects, for example) if you play the game at more than 30 frames per second (the physical WiiU default for BOTW).&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;Playing the game at higher framerates than recommended may also trigger unexpected glitches on quests, events, etc.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Lite Edited animations (SAFE):&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; About 80 animations from Full &amp;amp; Classic: Crouch, draw/hide weapons, end tired, jump, use Slate, open door, pick/throw objects, teleport. This option will demand less RAM to the game and may help to avoid infinite loading on a WiiU or a low end PC.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Classic edited animations (SAFER)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;: If you are getting severe trembling arms within the edited animations and it's not due the 30fps limit (or you don't want to change it), please install this safer option instead: you will get only the edited animations from version 8.4 (about 40 edits), that have been running for years without problems.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Default Link animations (SAFEST)&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Default Link animations will be used.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;EXTRA 1. Height of your hero&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;DEFAULT HEIGHT *&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;No changes at all. The height of your hero will be the one set by default or by its author.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Please note:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;Height variation is experimental, by telling the game to scale the player in a % value. It should work fine at least using values near to the default scale.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_hmore.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Tall (105%)&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Your hero will be 5% taller than her default height and will walk/run slightly faster too. The new height may affect in an almost unnoticeable way the hand placement on some two-handed objects, some clothes length and weapon range.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Taller (110%)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;: Your hero will be 10% taller than her default height and will walk/run a little faster too. The new height may very slightly affect hand placement on some two-handed objects, some clothes length and weapon range.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Tallest (115%)&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Your hero will be 15% taller than her default height and will walk/run faster too. The new height may affect two handed objects (a misaligned hand on the Slate or the paraglider), some clothes (some clippings, shorter tunics and skirts) and slightly extended weapon range (using swords, mostly).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_hless.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Short (95%)&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Your hero will be 5% shorter than her default height and will walk/run slightly slow too. The new height may affect in an almost unnoticeable way the hand placement on some two-handed objects, some clothes length and weapon range.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Shorter (90%)&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Your hero will be 10% shorter than her default height and will walk/run a little slow too. The new height may very slightly affect hand placement on some two-handed objects, clothes length and weapon range.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Shortest (85%)&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Your hero will be 15% shorter than her default height and will walk/run slower too. The new height may affect two handed objects (a misaligned hand on the Slate or the paraglider), some clothes (some clippings, longer tunics and skirts) and slightly reduced weapon range (using swords, mostly).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;EXTRA 2. BOTW Girly Logo replacement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Note: The logo replacement can be obtained as standalone mod&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; by&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i&gt;downloading the "Girly_Title_Replacement_Standalone.bnp"&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; (in case you're&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i&gt;using&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i&gt;an old version of the mod, for example).&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap99_0.png"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Nothing *&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;No changes on the current game logo will be made.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap99_1.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap99_2.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font color="#6ee16c"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Girly Silhouette &amp;amp; Heart&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;b&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Will replace the small bunch of flowers on the 'Z' form 'Zelda' word with a girl silhouette, and will add a small heart over the 'i' letter. This will only affect the game title logo on the main menu screen, while loading a savegame, etc.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap99lite_1.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap99lite_2.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Heart only&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Will add only a small heart over the 'i' on the 'Wild' word. This will only affect the game title logo on the main menu screen, while loading a savegame, etc.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;EXTRA 3. Optional patches&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Nothing *&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;No patch or anything will be installed.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_e2.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Unofficial Linkle 3 Patch Lite&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Lite version of my&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/441448"&gt;Unofficial Linkle 3 Patcher&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;mod. This one is included for convenience, and it just fixes Linkle 3 too&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;long arms&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;and adds a neck for compatibility with Linkle 2 mods. If you want the whole set of options, install the full Unofficial Linkle 3 Patch mod after the Girly Animation Pack (if you installed the Lite option, don’t worry as the complete mod will upgrade it without problems).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;BONUS ZIP FILE DOWNLOAD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Boot pictures in HD &amp;amp; Game Icon.zip&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap99def.png"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Default, AI upscale 1080p&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap99_3.png"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Girly Logo, 1080p&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap99lite_3.png"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Only heart, 1080p&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Download and unzip it in a folder to get the game boot pictures &lt;b&gt;AI upscaled to HD&lt;/b&gt;, and a &lt;b&gt;new icon&lt;/b&gt;. You will have the default BOTW logo design, and the two new Girly Logo replacements. To setup them in your game, check the &lt;b&gt;readme.txt&lt;/b&gt; file included in the ZIP.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_icon_emu.png"&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;nbsp;Game icon&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_trouble_c.png"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;What happened with version 9?&lt;/b&gt; I skipped it because the number nine is considered unlucky in some cultures. For example, in Japanese it sounds like the words for torture and suffering, and in Mandarin it sounds like death.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;We will have version 11? &lt;/b&gt;No. This is the end of the development for this mod. I will update it with bug-fixes when necessary, but I will not release a new version as I already spent an insane amount of time and everything I wanted to do, it's more or less done.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;When I try to build the mod with BCML using a ZIP file, my character seems to float a little over the ground.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;There is an unsolved bug in the final version of BCML, and you will get a faulty BNP. To avoid it you need to downgrade to BCML 3.8.0 (&lt;i&gt;as BCML has already ended its development cycle, it's not possible to address this issue, that's why a temporary downgrade is needed&lt;/i&gt;). To do it, &lt;u&gt;first uninstall any mod you may have&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;(it's a good idea to do it anyway to avoid any possible interference with other mods) then &lt;u&gt;close BCML&lt;/u&gt; and &lt;u&gt;open a command box&lt;/u&gt; (run "CMD" on Windows) and write:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; python -m pip install bcml==3.8.0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Once you get the BNP, you can upgrade again BCML as the bug only happens during the generation process (if you're using a different operating system or in case this is not working for you, just Google &lt;i&gt;how to downgrade a Python installed program&lt;/i&gt;, then change the name of that program to "BCML" and for the version, set it to "3.8.0". Thanks you and sorry for the inconveniences.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;I have [insert title replacement mod] installed, and I want the BOTW Girly Logo replacement too:&lt;/b&gt; This option will only replace the BOTW logo, not the artwork on the main menu. If you have another title replacement mod installed, just install the Girly Animation Pack AFTER it on BCML (as you should be already doing) to assure both mods will work together as much as possible: the logo from here, the artwork from the other one.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;I want the new icon and the screen we see while booting the game: &lt;/b&gt;You must download the bonus ZIP from the downloads section, unzip it in a folder and check the &lt;i&gt;readme &lt;/i&gt;file there for further instructions.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Why the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/413721" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow"&gt;Unofficial Linkle 3 Patch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;&amp;nbsp;is not available?&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; [&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Update:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/441448"&gt;Unofficial Linkle 3 Patcher&lt;/a&gt; now &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;online&lt;/span&gt;]&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;It was&amp;nbsp;trashed&amp;nbsp;by the Linkle 3 owners on 18/04/2023 for&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Copyright violation&lt;/em&gt;, out of the blue, after several months online. The unofficial patch&amp;nbsp;is recommended here and&amp;nbsp;widely used, but you can still install the&amp;nbsp;Lite version&amp;nbsp;included in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;Girly Animation Pack&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;(with authorization of Linkle 3 owners). It lacks of most of the backwards compatibility with Linkle 2, but its purpose here was to patch the long arms issue.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;I got arm trembling on some animations: &lt;/b&gt;A noticeable trembling may occur on arms on certain edited animations&amp;nbsp;(picking/throwing objects, for example) if you play the game at more than &lt;u&gt;30 frames per second&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;(the WiiU default for BOTW).&amp;nbsp;A light trembling may occur due the amateur edition process, but playing the game at higher framerates than recommended may trigger also other glitches on quests, events, etc. Please stick to the recommended settings when possible, thanks!&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Some transitions look bad, for example while still walking but just about to run:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;This happens when you mix very different styles of walking and running, for example Girly walk and Default running. In the description on each option and in the tooltips while installing, it’s explained what animations work best together.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;The mod never ends to install (Infinite loop on BCML):&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Avoid the 1-Click install option, and download the BNP file in a folder of your hard drive. Install the mod from that folder on BCML by pressing the “+” button. Ensure you check on option on each section when prompted. Ensure you have the latest BCML installed and also the latest version of the game (1.5.0 with DLC 3.0). If you have many mods installed, a good thing is to uninstall all of them except the player replacement one (Linkle, for example) then install Girly Animation Pack. If it works, then install some other mods, and keep trying the game until you find the mod causing the problem. Also, sometimes just uninstalling the mod and installing it again, or doing a remerge-all in BCML may fix the problem.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;My savegame never ends loading:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Uninstall the mod and install it again. Ensure you’re checking one option on each section, when prompted. On CEMU, ensure you have enabled in Graphic Packs, the mod called ''&lt;u&gt;Extended memory&lt;/u&gt;''. And as in the previous case, avoid the 1-Click install option, download the BNP to a folder then install it, do a remerge all in BCML, etc. Sometimes, rebooting the whole computer may help!&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;The game crasheswhen it’s about to play some animation or I get severe arms trembling: &lt;/b&gt;On some people, some edited animations included in the mod are incompatible with their game/setup. I can only suggest you to install the mod using the “SAFER” option where available and, if you still get problems, install the mod using the “SAFEST” options on each section. Since version 10, the only "SAFER" / "SAFEST" options are located in section 18, and animations should not crash with any player replacement (tested with Linkle 2, Linkle 3, Zelda's Ballad and default Link).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;I want to install &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/431101"&gt;Linkle Magical Girl&lt;/a&gt;, will it work?&lt;/b&gt; This amazing mod adds a whole set of&amp;nbsp; pretty new animations, luckily they're associated to the magic wand so installing it&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;is safe&lt;/span&gt;: it will work with Girly Animation Pack installed. Even more, it is also &lt;u&gt;backwards compatible&lt;/u&gt; with &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Linkle 2&lt;/span&gt;, as you can see in this small video:&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/linkle2_gap_magical_demo.apng"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;I have Second Wind mod, or Relics of the Past, or any other mod that does a lot of changes on the game or add custom animations:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;I can’t grant compatibility with those mods. Several users reported success when installing those mods after Girly Animation Pack, or after doing a remerge, or after reinstalling those mods… my mod purpose is to change some animations in the default game, and to do that some internal files needed to be modified and may conflict with changes made in those exact files by these other mods. It’s almost impossible for BCML to do a deep merge in those cases, at least currently, and for me/they it’s impossible to keep track of the changes every mod does in every game file in order to get fully compatibility.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_earsf.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;I got bouncing ears bug&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;using some headgear (like the Hylian Hood with Zelda's Ballad). That may occur using third-party armors replacements, and it’s not a Girly Animation Pack entirely issue. To solve it, a small mod has been developed and you can get it&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/344894"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_sizep.jpg"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;While gliding, one of the hands is misplaced, and while holding the slate with both hands, there is clipping on one of the hands: It seems to happen on most of the player replacements (Zelda's Ballad and Linkle). To solve it, please install this mod&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/391662"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_other_c.png"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul type="square"&gt;&lt;li&gt;M&lt;b&gt;akeup&lt;/b&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;earrings&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;glasses&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;for Linkle --&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/331562"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;dress&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Linkle is wearing in most of the shots --&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/skins/183741"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;haircut&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;used on most of the shots&amp;nbsp;--&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/skins/183137"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/skins/183508"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/skins/183508"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;And the&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;Clear Camera UI&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;mod to take clean shots --&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/296638"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
